==评价==
《地狱》一书获得的褒贬不一。《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》赞扬此书称其“充满各种小把戏”，并称小说“整本书都是布朗先生创造的惊心动魄的寻宝游戏”。<ref name="NYT">{{cite news |first=Janet |last=Maslin |title=On a Scavenger Hunt to Save Most Humans |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/13/books/inferno-by-dan-brown.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0 |work=The New York Times |date=2013-05-12 |accessdate=2013-05-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130614032251/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/13/books/inferno-by-dan-brown.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0 |archivedate=2013-06-14 }}</ref>《华盛顿邮报》认为，布朗在《地狱》中将“惊险的情节、奇怪的坏人及史诗般的背景三者交融的艺术发挥至完美”。《[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]》认为“该小说和《达·芬奇密码》一样寓教于乐”<ref name="chinawriter">{{cite web|url=http://www.chinawriter.com.cn/bk/2013-08-09/71616.html|title=丹·布朗新作《地狱》:空白叙事与伦理关怀|accessdate=2014-01-10|date=2013-08-09|publisher=中国作家网|author=朱振武|language=zh-cn|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407073422/http://www.chinawriter.com.cn/bk/2013-08-09/71616.html|archivedate=2014-04-07}}</ref>。《[[紐約每日新聞|紐約每日新聞]]》也给出了正面评价，称小说“穿插着密码信息、艺术史、科学和末日来临的摄人心魄的乐趣”。<ref name="NYDT">{{cite news |first=Sherryl |last=Connely |title=Dan Brown's powerful 'Inferno' thriller challenges readers with new puzzles based on Dante |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/dante-catholicism-fill-brown-sizzling-inferno-article-1.1343823 |work=Daily News (New York) |date=2013-05-14 |accessdate=2013-05-14 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606053043/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/dante-catholicism-fill-brown-sizzling-inferno-article-1.1343823 |archivedate=2013-06-06 }}</ref>

《[[独立报|独立报]]》评论家詹姆斯·基德（{{lang|en|James Kidd}}）则严厉批评了布朗糟糕的行文技巧，但对小说情节还是表示好感，他评价称：“布朗把哥特式的夸张手法和卖弄学问的旅行指南混杂在一起，糟糕的技巧限制了读者想象力的发挥。”<ref name="kidd">{{cite web|last=Kidd|first=James|title=Review: Inferno, By Dan Brown|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/reviews/review-inferno-by-dan-brown-8640760.html|publisher=''[[The_Independent|The Independent]]''|accessdate=2013-06-12|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608074152/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/reviews/review-inferno-by-dan-brown-8640760.html|archivedate=2013-06-08}}</ref>《[[波士顿环球报|波士顿环球报]]》评论家查克·雷迪（{{lang|en|Chuck Leddy}}）将这部小说与布朗之前的作品相比较，给出了正面评价，认为这部小说是“那种令人满足的可以逃避现实的读物，正适合在夏季阅读。”<ref name="leddy">{{cite web|last=Leddy|first=Chuck|title=‘Inferno’ by Dan Brown|url=http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/books/2013/05/26/book-review-inferno-dan-brown/TPxCswZpdIqLrkZHarRcYM/story.html|publisher=''The Boston Globe''|accessdate=2013-06-12|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607144031/http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/books/2013/05/26/book-review-inferno-dan-brown/TPxCswZpdIqLrkZHarRcYM/story.html|archivedate=2013-06-07}}</ref>[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]评论家萨马拉·阿米尔（{{lang|en|Samra Amir}}）认为小说情节完全在意料之中，对小说中的[[飛白|飛白]]也给出负面评价，但他还表示“布朗的艺术造诣使小说不那么无聊，他成功地吸引了读者的兴趣。”<ref name="amir">{{cite web|last=Amir|first=Samra|title=Book review: Dan Brown's Inferno - to hell with it|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/559153/book-review-dan-browns-inferno-to-hell-with-it/|publisher=''[[The_Express_Tribune|The Express Tribune]]''|accessdate=2013-06-12|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130611015226/http://tribune.com.pk/story/559153/book-review-dan-browns-inferno-to-hell-with-it/|archivedate=2013-06-11}}</ref>《[[卫报|卫报]]》评论家彼得·康拉德（{{lang|en|Peter Conrad}}）也评价称小说内容完全是“各种阴谋的大杂烩”，并补充说这本书“很可怕，充斥着白字和语法错误。而作者脑中似乎有一座挤满蝙蝠的钟楼，对外界的真实世界只有幼稚的明显错误的理解，书中还四处充斥着他这些错误理解的阴暗描写。”<ref name="conrad">{{cite web|last=Conrad|first=Peter|title=Inferno by Dan Brown – review|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2013/may/19/dan-brown-inferno-review|publisher=''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''|accessdate=2013-06-12|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607203120/http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2013/may/19/dan-brown-inferno-review|archivedate=2013-06-07}}</ref>

英国《[[卫报|卫报]]》称：“《地狱》将会是今年最热卖的图书。”《[[每日邮报|每日邮报]]》的评论员称：“尽管我觉得这部小说从头到尾都不靠谱，但我一读就会上瘾”<ref name="chinawriter"/>。在美国，本书在首发当日就登上了“纽约时报小说类畅销榜”榜首。在英国，本书的预购数超过[[J·K·罗琳|J·K·罗琳]]的《[[临时空缺|偶发空缺]]》所创下的记录<ref name="chinawriter"/>。丹布朗前几部小说的[[简体中文|简体中文]]翻译作者[[朱振武|朱振武]]则认为从“围绕人类未来所做的不同维度的探究”这一点来讲，本书是《失落的秘符》的姊妹篇<ref name="chinawriter"/>。

==商业表现==
《地狱》发行首周的全美销量高达369,000本，发行首周即登上美国畅销书排行榜冠军，但仍远低于他上一部作品《[[失落的秘符|失落的秘符]]》逾100万本的首周销量。英国首周销量也高达228,961本，位列英国畅销书排行榜冠军。第二周全美销量下滑42%，仅有211,000本，但这一数字依然远超[[卡勒德·胡賽尼|卡勒德·胡賽尼]]《{{link-en|群山回唱|And the Mountains Echoed|-{zh-cn:群山回唱;zh-tw:遠山的回音;}-}}》91,000本的销量，成为该周销量冠军。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/publisher-news/article/57357-inferno-has-huge-debut-but-below-the-lost-symbol.html|title='Inferno' Has Huge Debut, But Below 'The Lost Symbol'|work=Publishers Weekly|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608050146/http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/publisher-news/article/57357-inferno-has-huge-debut-but-below-the-lost-symbol.html|archivedate=2013-06-08|accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/publisher-news/article/57584-inferno-tops-hosseini.html|title='Inferno' Tops Hosseini|work=Publishers Weekly|date=2013-05-31|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407075713/http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/publisher-news/article/57584-inferno-tops-hosseini.html|archivedate=2014-04-07|accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref>

